<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="expectation-n">expectation <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌekspek'teɪʃn/    美 /ˌekspek'teɪʃn/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>期待；预期；期望：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>come / live up to / meet / answer sb's expectations</strong>
不负某人所望</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My teachers all have great <strong>expectations of</strong> me.
所有老师都对我有很高的期望。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They closed the windows in <strong>expectation of</strong> rain. 
他们预料会下雨，就关上了窗户。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="beyond-sbs-expectations">beyond (sb's) expectation(s)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>出乎 (某人) 意料地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It was an A+, which was beyond my modest expectations.
我得了个A+，这大大出乎我的意料。</p><footer>译林⑦ – 4</footer></div></div>